{"runId":"qwen-qwen3-32b-nitro@2026-05-13T22-21-58-423Z","slug":"beware-the-single-purpose-people","locale":"it","model":"qwen/qwen3-32b:nitro","modelPath":"qwen-qwen3-32b-nitro","createdAt":"2026-05-13T22:22:23.274Z","sourcePath":"src/content/posts/2025-04-03--beware-the-single-purpose-people/index.mdx","targetPath":"src/content/posts/2025-04-03--beware-the-single-purpose-people/it/index.mdx","candidatePath":"reports/i18n/beware-the-single-purpose-people/it/qwen-qwen3-32b-nitro/2026-05-13T22-21-58-423Z/candidate.mdx","sourceHash":"589549661808bbda140a93d1cc1d1b94e45f65803955211732aca6ca7dd257ab","outputHash":"4844051d7e0ea9d81b171e3ea111c349344cbbfe91c03ec0ba3e84204cbf36d4","reasoningEffort":"low","temperature":0.3,"maxTokens":16000,"timeoutMs":200000,"articleSummary":"The article argues that while the **Single Responsibility Principle (SRP)** promotes modularity and clarity, its rigid application—prioritizing \"small\" over \"cohesive\"—leads to **over-fragmented codebases** and reduced developer productivity. It critiques developers (dubbed \"Single-Purpose People\") who enforce arbitrary boundaries (e.g., 5-line functions), resulting in **file system shrapnel**, **dependency tangles**, and **testing fragility**, particularly in frameworks like React/Redux. The author advocates for **pragmatic SRP**: grouping logically related code that changes together, emphasizing **conceptual cohesion** over atomicity. The tone is analytical and cautionary, using metaphors like \"Unix philosophy\" and \"Rube Goldberg Pattern\" to contrast idealism with practicality. Intended for developers and architects grappling with modular design","totalInputTokens":6379,"totalOutputTokens":6121,"totalCacheReadTokens":2048,"totalCacheWriteTokens":0,"totalDurationMs":13815,"totalCostUsd":0.00197936,"pricingSource":"local-openrouter-estimate","telemetry":{"model":"qwen/qwen3-32b:nitro","chunkSize":"10p","totalChunks":5,"totalInputTokens":6379,"totalOutputTokens":6121,"totalCacheReadTokens":2048,"totalCacheWriteTokens":0,"totalDurationMs":13815,"totalCostUsd":0.00197936,"pricingSource":"local-openrouter-estimate","chunks":[{"index":0,"inputTokens":1113,"outputTokens":1434,"cacheReadTokens":0,"cacheWriteTokens":0,"durationMs":3120,"costUsd":0.0004332},{"index":1,"inputTokens":1488,"outputTokens":1298,"cacheReadTokens":512,"cacheWriteTokens":0,"durationMs":3127,"costUsd":0.00043055999999999997},{"index":2,"inputTokens":1285,"outputTokens":1007,"cacheReadTokens":512,"cacheWriteTokens":0,"durationMs":2304,"costUsd":0.00034448},{"index":3,"inputTokens":1507,"outputTokens":1614,"cacheReadTokens":512,"cacheWriteTokens":0,"durationMs":3616,"costUsd":0.00050792},{"index":4,"inputTokens":986,"outputTokens":768,"cacheReadTokens":512,"cacheWriteTokens":0,"durationMs":1648,"costUsd":0.0002632}]}}
{"runId":"qwen-qwen3.6-35b-a3b@2026-05-13T22-21-08-432Z","slug":"beware-the-single-purpose-people","locale":"hi","model":"qwen/qwen3.6-35b-a3b","modelPath":"qwen-qwen3.6-35b-a3b","createdAt":"2026-05-13T22:23:57.990Z","sourcePath":"src/content/posts/2025-04-03--beware-the-single-purpose-people/index.mdx","targetPath":"src/content/posts/2025-04-03--beware-the-single-purpose-people/hi/index.mdx","candidatePath":"reports/i18n/beware-the-single-purpose-people/hi/qwen-qwen3.6-35b-a3b/2026-05-13T22-21-08-432Z/candidate.mdx","sourceHash":"589549661808bbda140a93d1cc1d1b94e45f65803955211732aca6ca7dd257ab","outputHash":"55c8c100b346a06621574348a2d78e0b4f045e072bee734da7b2edf773ea153f","reasoningEffort":"low","temperature":0.3,"maxTokens":16000,"timeoutMs":200000,"articleSummary":"This article critiques the dogmatic application of the Single Responsibility Principle (SRP), arguing that developers who prioritize arbitrary code size limits over conceptual cohesion produce fragmented, unmaintainable architectures. Drawing on examples from React/Redux and Unix philosophy, the author demonstrates how over-fragmentation creates \"file system shrapnel,\" brittle tests, and excessive cognitive load that severely hampers development velocity. Written as a critical yet pragmatic analysis with a satirical/rant-like edge, the piece relies heavily on architectural and structural metaphors (e.g., \"dismembered architecture,\" \"Rube Goldberg patterns,\" \"archaeological digs\") to frame the issue. It targets software engineers, architects, and engineering managers seeking to replace rigid modularity rules with cohesive, pragmatic design practices.","totalInputTokens":6752,"totalOutputTokens":32259,"totalCacheReadTokens":0,"totalCacheWriteTokens":0,"totalDurationMs":140286,"totalCostUsd":0.0332718,"pricingSource":"local-openrouter-estimate","telemetry":{"model":"qwen/qwen3.6-35b-a3b","chunkSize":"10p","totalChunks":5,"totalInputTokens":6752,"totalOutputTokens":32259,"totalCacheReadTokens":0,"totalCacheWriteTokens":0,"totalDurationMs":140286,"totalCostUsd":0.0332718,"pricingSource":"local-openrouter-estimate","chunks":[{"index":0,"inputTokens":1140,"outputTokens":6771,"cacheReadTokens":0,"cacheWriteTokens":0,"durationMs":29246,"costUsd":0.006942},{"index":1,"inputTokens":1560,"outputTokens":8401,"cacheReadTokens":0,"cacheWriteTokens":0,"durationMs":36643,"costUsd":0.008635},{"index":2,"inputTokens":1380,"outputTokens":6251,"cacheReadTokens":0,"cacheWriteTokens":0,"durationMs":27171,"costUsd":0.006457999999999999},{"index":3,"inputTokens":1591,"outputTokens":7854,"cacheReadTokens":0,"cacheWriteTokens":0,"durationMs":33639,"costUsd":0.00809265},{"index":4,"inputTokens":1081,"outputTokens":2982,"cacheReadTokens":0,"cacheWriteTokens":0,"durationMs":13587,"costUsd":0.0031441499999999996}]}}
{"runId":"qwen-qwen3.6-35b-a3b@2026-05-13T22-22-23-827Z","slug":"beware-the-single-purpose-people","locale":"it","model":"qwen/qwen3.6-35b-a3b","modelPath":"qwen-qwen3.6-35b-a3b","createdAt":"2026-05-13T22:24:24.361Z","sourcePath":"src/content/posts/2025-04-03--beware-the-single-purpose-people/index.mdx","targetPath":"src/content/posts/2025-04-03--beware-the-single-purpose-people/it/index.mdx","candidatePath":"reports/i18n/beware-the-single-purpose-people/it/qwen-qwen3.6-35b-a3b/2026-05-13T22-22-23-827Z/candidate.mdx","sourceHash":"589549661808bbda140a93d1cc1d1b94e45f65803955211732aca6ca7dd257ab","outputHash":"53eb808daadee75bd33be33e3d25491f22c4916355ffaee03ed34384dc022f02","reasoningEffort":"low","temperature":0.3,"maxTokens":16000,"timeoutMs":200000,"articleSummary":"This article argues that while the Single Responsibility Principle (SRP) is fundamentally sound, its rigid enforcement as extreme code atomization degrades maintainability, inflates cognitive load, and stifles development velocity. Targeted at software developers and engineering architects, the piece adopts a cautionary yet pragmatic tone, using the framing device of \"Single-Purpose People\" to critique dogmatic adherence to arbitrary metrics like line counts. Through recurring metaphors such as \"MC Escher\" and \"Rube Goldberg\" architectures, the author contrasts pathological fragmentation with healthy cohesion, drawing on pragmatic examples like the Unix philosophy while critiquing over-engineered stacks like React/Redux. Ultimately, it advocates grouping related functionality based on shared change patterns and conceptual boundaries rather than theoretical purity.","totalInputTokens":6397,"totalOutputTokens":23652,"totalCacheReadTokens":0,"totalCacheWriteTokens":0,"totalDurationMs":102834,"totalCostUsd":0.02461155,"pricingSource":"local-openrouter-estimate","telemetry":{"model":"qwen/qwen3.6-35b-a3b","chunkSize":"10p","totalChunks":5,"totalInputTokens":6397,"totalOutputTokens":23652,"totalCache